{
  "texts": [
    "The pioneering work in applying HSI reconstruction to agri-food samples was conducted by Zhao et al. (2020b).",
    "Their study implemented the HSCNN-R algorithm to evaluate various parameters, including soluble solid content (SSC), total titratable acidity (TTA), and lycopene content in 33 tomato samples.",
    "The outcomes, characterized by an RMSE of 6.22, MRAE of 0.05, and SAM of 1.68, highlighted the reconstruction algorithm's training performance.",
    "However, the study also identified significant discrepancies between the reconstructed and ground-truth (GT) spectral data within the 380-740 nm range.",
    "This discrepancy led to less accurate predictions for SSC and TTA (listed in Table 2), underscoring the challenges in achieving precise HSI reconstruction for these quality parameters."
  ]
}